    <section role="standard">
      <title><indexterm>
          <primary>Purchase Orders</primary>
          <secondary>electronic delivery of</secondary>
        </indexterm><indexterm>
          <primary>electronic data interchange</primary>
          <secondary>Purchase Order delivery using</secondary>
        </indexterm>Send Electronic Purchase Order</title>
      <para>To send a copy of a Purchase Order electronically, select the
      "Send Electronic Purchase Order" option. The following screen will
      appear:</para>
      <screenshot>
        <mediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="???" />
          </imageobject>
          <caption><para>E-mail Purchase Order
          Form</para><para><remark>findme: get a screenshot of the submitEDI
          window with the open list or search of purchase
          orders</remark></para></caption>
        </mediaobject>
      </screenshot>
      <para>This window shows either a list or search window for Purchase
      Orders for those Vendors configured to receive EDI. You are presented
      with the following options:</para>
      <variablelist>
        <varlistentry>
          <term>Search for</term>
          <listitem>
            <para>Optionally enter an Purchase Order number here to find it in
            the list.</para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
          <term>Orders</term>
          <listitem>
            <para>List of Purchase Orders that can be sent by EDI.</para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
      </variablelist>
      <note>
        <para>Vendors are set up to receive electronic deliveries of
        information using the "Transmission" tab on the Vendor master.</para>
      </note>
      <para>To the far right of the screen, the following buttons are
      available:</para>
      <variablelist>
        <varlistentry>
          <term>CANCEL</term>
          <listitem>
            <para>Closes the screen without scheduling a Purchase Order for
            delivery, returning you to the application desktop.</para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
          <term>SELECT</term>
          <listitem>
            <para>Select the Purchase Order for delivery. This closes the
            window and proceeds to sending the EDI.</para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
      </variablelist>
      <xi:include href="guiclient/submitEDI.xml" xpointer="submitEDI"
                  xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" />
    </section>
  </section>
